6543/ }}\n* {{cite book | last=Rodgers | first=Cleveland | title=Robert Moses: Builder for Democracy | publisher=Holt | year=1952 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Dp0YAAAAYAAJ }}\n* {{cite book |last=Vidal |first=Gore |title=What Robert Moses Did to New York City |work=New York Review of Books |date=October 17, 1974}}\n{{refend}}\n\n===Other sources===\n{{refbegin}}\n'''Exhibits:'''\n*[http://web.mta.info/bandt/images/tribcelebrate.htm \"The Triborough Bridge: Robert Moses and the Automobile Age\"]{{dead link|date=December 2016}} exhibit at the New York Transit Museum (through April 2008)\n*[http://www.learn.columbia.edu/moses/ \"Robert Moses and the Modern City\"] exhibit February 2007 thru May 2007 at 3 New York City museums\n*[http://www.metropolismag.com/December-1969/Looking-Back-at-Moses/ \"Looking Back at Moses\"] a trio of New York museums\n*[http://pureandapplied.com/robert-moses/ Photographs from the Museum of the City of New York exhibit]\n\n'''Papers:'''\n*[http://archives.nypl.org/mss/2071 Robert Moses papers, 1912\u20131980], held by the Manuscripts and Archives Division, [[New York Public Library]]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20010502174335/http://www.nycroads.com/crossings/LI-sound-4/ Online letters of Moses]\n\n'''Archival Audio:'''\n* [http://www.wnyc.org/series/robert-moses/ The Robert Moses Collection] at [http://wnyc.org/archives The WNYC Archives]\n\n'''Interviews:'''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20021022175808/http://www.wiredforbooks.org/robertmoses/ 1973 audio interview of Robert Moses by Don Swaim of CBS Radio, RealAudio at Wired for Books.org]\n*[https://archive.org/details/openmind_ep226 Robert A. Caro talks to Richard D. Heffner about Robert Moses on the Open Mind, 1998]\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote|Robert Moses}}\n{{Commons category|Robert Moses}}\n* {{Internet Archive film clip|id=gov.archives.arc.95822|description=\"Longines Chronoscope with Robert Moses  (February 11, 1953)\"}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\